{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d8b290b0-34a7-422d-a25d-d5ac508a633f","content":"With **MSTest 3.8.2** on .NET 9, you get full constructor injection support. Here's the recommended pattern:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests\n{\n    private readonly TestContext _testContext;\n    private MyService _service;\n\n    // Synchronous init via constructor — TestContext is injected automatically\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        _testContext = testContext;\n    }\n\n    // Async init runs after the constructor, before each test\n    [TestInitialize]\n    public async Task SetupAsync()\n    {\n        _service = await MyService.CreateAsync();\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void SyncTest()\n    {\n        Assert.IsNotNull(_testContext);\n        Assert.IsNotNull(_service);\n    }\n\n    [TestCleanup]\n    public async Task CleanupAsync()\n    {\n        await _service.DisposeAsync();\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- **Constructor** — handles synchronous setup; `TestContext` is injected automatically (no property needed).\n- **`[TestInitialize]`** — return `async Task` for async setup; runs before each test.\n- **Execution order:** Constructor → `[TestInitialize]` → Test → `[TestCleanup]`.\n- Avoid `async void` — always use `async Task` for async init/cleanup methods.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"94cb148d-5dd3-4817-8977-da0988ad0043","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"They're using MSTest 3.8.2 on .NET 9.0. In modern MSTest (v3+), constructor injection for `TestContext` is supported. Let me provide the recommended pattern.\n\nIn MSTest v3+, you can:\n1. Inject `TestContext` via the constructor\n2. Use `[TestInitialize]` for synchronous init (though constructors work too)\n3. Use `[TestInitialize]` with `async Task` for async init\n\nActually, let me be precise. In MSTest 3.x:\n- Constructor injection of `TestContext` is supported\n- `[TestInitialize]` can be async (return `Task`)\n\n\n- Class-level setup and teardown use `[ClassInitialize]` and `[ClassCleanup]`, which run before the constructor\n\nThe best approach is to inject `TestContext` through the constructor for synchronous setup, then use `[TestInitialize]` as an async method when you need to handle async operations.","outputTokens":588,"requestId":"E3D1:321F09:68BC0C:7842B7:6A05284A"},"id":"eec336d9-04b1-4a5f-9511-11cf1f4e2381","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:41:42.783Z","parentId":"e288764a-23cc-4f27-a1b1-77b364ce699b"}
